Packages 
Package Description
gui.analyzer
GUI analyzer package.
gui.analyzer.aspects
Aspects for registering the listeners to the main application, running the DEAL prototype and generating domain models.
gui.analyzer.aspects.components
These aspects work only with a special version of Java, and are not active in this DEAL version.
gui.analyzer.handlers  
gui.analyzer.handlers.jscicalc

gui.analyzer.handlers.swing  
gui.analyzer.handlers.swing.record  
gui.analyzer.statistics
Experimental statistics.
gui.analyzer.util
Utility classes for handling Components, JLabels, Logging and Strings.
gui.editor  
gui.editor.tabpane  
gui.editor.tree  
gui.generator.dsl  
gui.generator.itask  
gui.model
Classes representing the application model and the domain model.
gui.model.application
Classes encapsulating the application with an application model.
gui.model.application.componentPath  
gui.model.application.events
Classes encapsulating the events and event sequences, which were performed by a user on a GUI.
gui.model.application.observable
Classes for observing the changes in the Application model.
gui.model.application.program
The support for the replay function.
gui.model.application.scenes
The classes encapsulating the user interface scenes (windows, dialogs, frames, web pages, etc.)
gui.model.application.webpage  
gui.model.domain
Classes defining the domain model.
gui.model.domain.constraint
Classes defining the constraints for the terms in the domain model.
gui.model.domain.relation
The package for relations is unused in the actual project, it is however planned to be used in the future.
gui.tools
DEAL tools: DEAL method classes (DuplicateSceneDetector, DomainModelGenerator, Extractor, Simplifier) and classes implementing the record and replay functionality.
